SIMPLE: clique
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Clique
<hw>Clique</hw> <pr>(kl⟦emac⟧k)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr.
OF. <ets>cliquer</ets> to click. See <er>Click</er>, <pos>v.
i.</pos>]</ety> <def>A narrow circle of persons associated by common
interests or for the accomplishment of a common purpose; -- generally
used in a bad sense.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Clique</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Clique
<hw>Clique</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To To associate together in a
clannish way; to act with others secretly to gain a desired end; to
plot; -- used with <ptcl>together</ptcl>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>cliquish</ent>⟦br⟧
